cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.NE 

This paper is about image super-resolution using deep learning methods, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of image transform domain, which suggests a possible fit with cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The regularization techniques used in the proposed network structure also suggest a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
